# Vedic Astrology Documentation Rules

## Hindi Names for Planets and Rashis

Always use Hindi names (in Devanagari script) with English translations when referring to planets and zodiac signs:

### Planets (Grahas)
- Sun = <span className="hindi">सूर्य</span> (Surya)
- Moon = <span className="hindi">चंद्र</span> (Chandra)
- Mars = <span className="hindi">मंगल</span> (Mangala)
- Mercury = <span className="hindi">बुध</span> (Budha)
- Jupiter = <span className="hindi">गुरु</span> (Guru)
- Venus = <span className="hindi">शुक्र</span> (Shukra)
- Saturn = <span className="hindi">शनि</span> (Shani)
- Rahu = <span className="hindi">राहु</span> (Rahu)
- Ketu = <span className="hindi">केतु</span> (Ketu)

### Zodiac Signs (Rashis)
- Aries = <span className="hindi">मेष</span> (Mesha)
- Taurus = <span className="hindi">वृषभ</span> (Vrishabha)
- Gemini = <span className="hindi">मिथुन</span> (Mithuna)
- Cancer = <span className="hindi">कर्क</span> (Karka)
- Leo = <span className="hindi">सिंह</span> (Simha)
- Virgo = <span className="hindi">कन्या</span> (Kanya)
- Libra = <span className="hindi">तुला</span> (Tula)
- Scorpio = <span className="hindi">वृश्चिक</span> (Vrishchika)
- Sagittarius = <span className="hindi">धनु</span> (Dhanu)
- Capricorn = <span className="hindi">मकर</span> (Makara)
- Aquarius = <span className="hindi">कुंभ</span> (Kumbha)
- Pisces = <span className="hindi">मीन</span> (Meena)

### Nakshatras
Keep nakshatra names in Hindi when used in context.

## Usage Guidelines

1. First mention: Use both Hindi and English with translation
   Example: <span className="hindi">गुरु</span> (Jupiter)

2. Subsequent mentions: Use Hindi name only
   Example: <span className="hindi">गुरु</span>

3. In tables: Use Hindi names with className="hindi" styling

4. Hindi text styling: Always wrap Hindi text in <span className="hindi">...</span>

5. Technical terms in Hindi should also be styled:
   - <span className="hindi">दशा</span> (Dasha)
   - <span className="hindi">योग</span> (Yoga)
   - <span className="hindi">दृष्टि</span> (Drishti)
   - <span className="hindi">ग्रह</span> (Graha)
   - <span className="hindi">राशि</span> (Rashi)

## CSS Styling

Hindi text is styled via globals.css:
```css
.hindi {
  font-weight: 500;
  color: #667eea;
}

.dark .hindi {
  color: #a78bfa;
}
```

Purple in light mode, light purple in dark mode.

